      <prefercite id="aspace_46b133c3f7b8c43d5a5d1ea2b0bea53a">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>James Harvey Linsley Family Papers (MS 1424). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_efaa2f880541937fc4016fff47429ca1">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The James Harvey Linsley Family Papers consist of correspondence, writings, notebooks, and other papers of several member of the Linsley family. The bulk of the material reflects James Harvey Linsley's interests. Two notebooks contain his notes and catalogs of shells and botanical terms, while a scrapbook contains clippings of his writings on political and agricultural topics as printed in the <title render="italic">
               <part>Gospel Witness</part>
            </title> and the <title render="italic">
               <part>Republican Farmer</part>
            </title>. The papers also contain a notebook kept by Linsley at Yale College.</p>
         <p>Papers of Jesse Linsley and Reuben Linsley relate to North Branford, Connecticut, where James Harvey Linsley was born. These papers include an account book of Jesse Linsley and an inventory of the estate of Reuben Linsley showing the division of property between his daughter Polly and his widow Tryphena Linsley.</p>
         <p>Papers of James Halsey Linsley relate to his education at the normal school in New Britain, Connecticut and his teaching career. His compositions include instructions on how to teach. James Halsey Linsley's relation to the other Linsley family members represented in the papers is unclear.</p>
         <p>The Linsley Papers were transferred from the Miscellaneous Manuscripts Collection (MS 352) in 1985. Some of the papers were donated to the Yale Library by William Lyon Phelps, a grandson of James Harvey Linsley, while others were apparently purchased from a dealer.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
